[3
Date: Wed 28 Nov 2001
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: The Malaysian National News Agency, 26 Nov 2001 [edited

Malaysia: Dengue fever outbreak close to end
--------------------------------------------
A total of 497 confirmed dengue cases were detected between 1 Jan and 17
Nov 2001 in Penang, state executive councillor for health Dr K Rajapathy
said today [Wed 28 Nov. Of the total, 254 cases were detected in the
island and the rest in Seberang Perai on the mainland; 39 of these were
dengue hemorrhagic fever.
[Of the recent cases, 198 confirmed dengue fever were reported in 3 areas;
Lorong Sungai Dua (144), Tanjung Tokong Police Barracks (29) and Taman Free
School (25). Dr Rajapathy said that Taman Free School was declared
dengue-free on 23 Nov 2001, while Tanjung Tokong police barracks would be
declared the same on 30 Nov 2001 if no fresh cases were reported. The last
dengue case in the area was detected on 16 Nov 2001. He said Lorong Sungai
Dua would be declared free from dengue on 2 Dec 2001 as the last case was
reported on 18 Nov 2001.
Meanwhile, acting state health director Dr Azmi Shafie said the department
had issued 98 compounds [sic to 12 houses in Sungai Dua, Taman Free School
(78) and 8 in Tanjung Tokong Police Barracks. A total of 345 000 premises
were checked and 1550 compounds [sic were issued as they were found to
have mosquito breeding grounds, he added.
